Arab League to Discuss Libya Turmoil Tomorrow, Jazeera Says
The Arab League will meet tomorrow to discuss the turmoil in Libya, Al-Jazeera reported.
Qatari Prime Minister Sheikh Hamad Bin Jasim Bin Jaber Al-Thani called Amr Moussa the secretary general of the Cairo-based league today to call for the convening of the organization, the Doha-based news channel reported.
Qatarâ€™s foreign ministry condemned the use of air power and weapons against the Libyan people, the TV news channel reported.